==English==
===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[μυριάδος]]''' (''myriados''), genetive of '''[[μυριάς]]''' (''myrias'') "number of 10,000", from '''[[μύριος]]''' (''myrios'') "numberless, countless, infinite".

===Adjective===
'''myriad'''
# Great in number; [[innumerable]].

===Noun===
'''myriad'''
# {{archaic}} [[ten thousand|Ten thousand]].
# A [[vast]] [[diversity]] or number.
#: ''Earth hosts '''myriad''' animals.''

